                <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 tracking-tight">
                    What is a Companies House Confirmation Statement?
                </h2>
                <p>
                    A **companies house confirmation statement** (formerly known as the annual return) is a statutory document that every active and dormant UK Limited company must submit once a year. The purpose of the CS01 filing is to confirm that the information Companies House holds about your business—such as directors, office address, share structures, and People with Significant Control (PSCs)—is accurate and up to date.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Even if your company has had zero changes over the past 12 months, you are still legally required to review the record and file a confirmation statement. The filing window opens exactly 1 year after your incorporation date (or the date of your last statement) and closes 14 days later.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Failing to file your confirmation statement on time is a criminal offense under the UK Companies Act. It can lead to the prosecution of directors, severe court fines, and the eventual forced strike-off and dissolution of your company. Once dissolved, all assets—including your corporate bank balances—automatically become Crown property.
                </p>
                <div class="p-6 bg-blue-50/50 rounded-2xl border border-blue-100 mt-6">
